.TH CENTRE 3S "Sphinx Informix Tools"
.SH NAME
centre \(em centre a string
.SH SYNOPSIS
function \fBcentre\fP(s, i)
 define
  s char(80),
  i integer
 ...
 return s
.br
end function
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBCentre\fP takes the string passed as an argument and
centres it in a field whose width is specified by the
second argument.
This is useful in reports for getting headings and other
strings centred.
